<br>
&quot;Thank-you Metallica for making Metal Music&quot;<br>
<br>
*rolls on floor laughing hysterically*<br>
<br>
Ok now this could be taken two ways....<br>
<br>
Thank-you Metallica for being a band and making metal music.<br>
<br>
Or <br>
<br>
Thank-you Metallica for making Metal Music what it is today.<br>
<br>
Here is my response to both meanings.<br>
<br>
Please the last album that Metallica made that was good was The Black album. Ever since then your music has sounded like a bunch of over the hill grandpa's trying to sound like every other thrasher band out there. Your new album is crap and I cring when I think that I had to pay 20 bucks to figure that out. I have finally lost faith in you after I heard the lastest accident that you call a CD.<br>
<br>
And if I offended anyone with this post, I am sorry that is just how I feel. Maybe if more bands would stay true to what made them fans in the first place they would not turn there backs on us and then expect us to buy there new shit!<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Haivane Dragonfyre<br>
<br>
