Bands who make albums just to please an audience are mostly not very creative.<br>
<br>
Metallica definately helped making metal what it is today, most of todays metal bands has some metallica in them, it's not the other way around.<br>
<br>
I think you contradict yourself when you first say 'grandpa's trying to sound like every other thrasher band out there' and then 'if more bands would stay true to what made them fans in the first place they would not turn there backs on us'<br>
Metallica pretty much invented trash metal, if they sound like every other trasher band it's BECAUSE they have stayed true to what made them famous.<br>
<br>
Their new album definately isn't one of their best, but i personally think it's better than half the albums they released in the 90s, it's also very different from their previous albums, just like most of their albums are different from eachother.<br>
<br>
It's change and getting new audiences that has kept them alive for almost 20 years, most of their current fans were probably wearing diapers when they started out in the mid 80s. :P<br>
<br>
Kudos to Metallica for saving us from a world of 'Power ballads'!!!<br>
(Wich is where metal was heading when Metallica broke the trend.)<br>
